Data Production Engineer		Placemeter		NEW YORK		<div class="rich-text" itemprop="description"><p>We are looking for a junior <strong>Data Production Engineer</strong>. As a member of Placemeter's Computer Vision team you will be the crucial link between algorithm development and production data delivery. You will analyze data produced by our algorithms from real-world video, evaluate its quality, identify problems and work on solutions together with Computer Vision engineers. You'll also manage our large QA video database against which we test any code changes. </p><p></p><p>This position is ideal for an entry-level engineer with a strong interest in data-crunching who wants to gain more experience in Computer Vision. </p><p></p><p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong> </p><ul><li>Manage the QA process for new and existing algorithms </li><li>Develop and maintain tools to monitor data and algorithm quality </li><li>Identify and diagnose weaknesses in our algorithm stack </li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong> </p><ul><li>BS in a technical field or equivalent experience </li><li>Some experience with Computer Vision or data analytics </li><li>Good Python programming skills </li><li>Bonus: Practical C++ experience </li><li>Ability to work in a fast-paced startup environment </li></ul><p>We will consider candidates both at our headquarters in New York and at our satellite office in Paris (France). To apply for New York you have to be already authorized to work in the US (i.e., be a citizen or have a Green Card). We cannot sponsor a US visa for this position, sorry. </p><p></p><p><strong>About Placemeter</strong> </p><p><strong> </strong> </p><p>Founded in 2012 and based in New York City, Placemeter is an urban intelligence platform. We quantify the movement of modern cities, at scale. </p><p></p><p>Placemeter ingests any kind of video to analyze pedestrian and vehicular movement, revealing hidden patterns and strategic opportunities. We use proprietary computer vision technology to gather data from live streams and archival video. We take privacy very seriously, designing our systems to yield useful data without identity detection. </p><p></p><p>Learn more about us at www.placemeter.com</p></div><div class="rich-text" itemprop="description"></div>